The article discusses the dispute over Republican claims about the effectiveness of the Recovery Act. It highlights a CNN segment challenging John Boehner's statement that no federally funded economic recovery projects have started in Ohio. The segment features a Republican sheriff from Boehner's district who received nearly $1 million in economic recovery funds and used it to keep correctional officers on staff. The article also mentions a fact-checking piece by CNN on an ad from Boehner claiming he was still looking for jobs created by the Recovery Act. The article cites Politifact.org, which found that Boehner's claims were not supported by the facts. The article emphasizes the importance of fact-checking and highlights that many claims are being made without attention to the facts.